headline: Cocoa Prices Recover as Ivory Coast Cocoa Deliveries Slow
summary: December ICE NY cocoa (CCZ25 ) today is up +62 (+1.03%), and December ICE London cocoa #7 (CAZ25 ) is up +18 (+0.42%). Cocoa prices recovered from 1.5-week lows today and moved higher on signs of a slowdown in cocoa exports from the Ivory Coast, the world's largest cocoa producer....

headline: Dark Chocolate Market Report 2025: Players Analysis, Recent Developments, Strategies, Sustainability, Product Launches, Key Persons, and Revenue Forecasts 2024-2033
summary: The dark chocolate industry is set to thrive, expected to surpass US$ 130.58 Billion by 2033, doubling from US$ 66.37 Billion in 2024, at a CAGR of 7.81%. Growing awareness of health benefits, driven by antioxidants and polyphenols, fuels global market expansion. headline: 3 Consumer Stocks That Concern Us
summary: Consumer staples are considered safe havens in turbulent markets due to their inelastic demand profiles. On the other hand, they usually underperform during bull runs, and this paradigm has rung true over the past six months as the sector’s -8.9% decline paled in comparison to the S&P 500’s 15.3% gain.
